"37:65:1" : {s: 37, a: 65, w: 1, r: "طلع", t: "طَلْعُهَا", l: "طَلْع", lc: 4, tl: "ṭalʿuhā", lb: "খেজুর গাছের শীষ, মঞ্জরী, কলি",e: "Its emerging fruit", b: "তার ছড়াগুলো (হচ্ছে এমন)", i: "dahannya/buahnya", f: 2, rm: "to ascend/rise, go up, learn, come on, come towards anyone, start from, climb upon, reach, sprout, notice, look, seek, examine, expose, explain, appear, inform, occur, consider, know. talun - the spathe or sheath in which the flowers of the date palm are enclosed, also the fruit when it first appears, fruit, ranged dates. tuluu - rising. matlaun - twilight of rising (of sun). atlaa (vb. 4) - to make manifest to anyone, cause one to understand. ittalaa for ittaalaa (vb. 8) - to mount up, penetrate. attalaa for aattalaa - has he penetrated (here the hamzah of union waslah being omitted after the interrogative hamzah).", ag: "أسم مرفوع وضمير متصل ", eg: "Noun Nominative case and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "طَلْعٌۭ،تَطَّلِعُ،أَطَّلِعُ"},
